            "description": "I spent seven months on my Master thesis project titled \"Effect of metal oxide supports on active-Cu for CO/CO2 hydrogenation to methanol\". In this project, I study the effect of different oxide promoters with respect to conversion and selectivity. During this project, I have learned various characterisation techniques used to determine physical and chemical composition of the particle. Besides this, I have successfully modeled the PFR used in the experiment using MATLAB. Moreover, I came up with two new catalyst bed configurations for improved selectivity towards methanol.\nI was also responsible for setting up the reactor, gas chromatograph prior to starting the experimental work.",
