            },
            "description": "I was involved in the conceptual design of a process to recover heat from the flue gases in an Oxy steel plant at TATA steel, IJmuiden with a team of 3 fellow students of Chemical engineering. The main objective was to recover heat from flue gases exiting oxy-steel furnace at a temperature > 1600 deg C. \nWe came up with two innovative solutions to recover the heat and convert the process from batch to continuous. One of the solutions involved producing new molecules using a reactor in conjunction with a phase change material to recover heat.",
