                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 7,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2019
                }
            },
            "description": "I was a part of six member team, wherein a conceptual and detailed design of storing hydrogen in LOHC was done. The hydrogen was obtained from intermittent renewable energy and was reacted with other hydrocarbons, in order to be used as a source of fuel. This project was done in collaboration with Shell.\nI was responsible for the detailed design of reactor and other vessels and heat exchangers. Moreover, I performed a HAZOP study for the entire plant. The size of the plant designed was similar to a refuelling station. However, it was concluded that the hydrocarbon used to store hydrogen should have higher boiling point.",
